.Python

# ── Generated data assets ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# assets/cities.tsv            ← committed (260 KB stub → replaced by setup)
# assets/cities_precise.tsv   ← stub committed; run scripts/fetch_cities.py
# assets/cities_detailed.tsv  ← stub committed; run scripts/fetch_cities.py
# assets/ports.tsv             ← stub committed; run scripts/fetch_ports.py
#
# The stubs (header row only) are committed so Flutter can build without running
# the setup scripts first.  After running the scripts, git update-index marks
# these files as skip-worktree so local changes are not staged accidentally:
#
#   git update-index --skip-worktree \
#       assets/cities_precise.tsv \
#       assets/cities_detailed.tsv \
#       assets/ports.tsv
#
# To reset a file back to the stub (e.g. after a git pull):
#   git update-index --no-skip-worktree assets/cities_precise.tsv
#   git checkout -- assets/cities_precise.tsv
#
# assets/icon/app_icon.png     ← committed (generated by scripts/generate_icon.py)
# assets/icon/app_icon_fg.png  ← committed

# ── Raw upstream data (NOT in repo — download from source) ───────────────────
# data/UpdatedPub150.csv  ← NGA WPI raw CSV; download from NGA or pass as
#                            --wpi-file to scripts/fetch_ports.py
data/

# ── Python script cache ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

